Notes: Felt ok, decent pace, bit of blocked sinuses and something on chest, but got round in ok time despite mud and slippery sections in woods. Pleased to have reached 1200km this year \o/
Good run, felt strong, annoying GPS drop out coming down from top of Meadows. Right thigh/hop felt ok.
Felt good, right thigh ok for most of it. Was cold and icey in places but better than previous days.
Very, very icy and slippery underfoot, hence went very slowly, really enjoyed from about 2/3 in though. Right thigh not too bad.
Cold and icy under foot so went slowly, right thigh ok, bit sore/stiff but got round and is loosened up after a while.
Felt ok, didn't push hard at first but did a bit after 3km, decent pace maintained, right hip noticeable but not sore at all.
First time in the woods for a while, hard going on the hills and slippery underfoot, but right leg/hip wasn't too bad and kept going for a bit longer to reach the yearly goal of 1200km.
Not too bad, right thigh/hip/glute still sore, migrated to lower back by end

Terrible run, hate going out in the evening and dark. Tight chest, start of cold/respiratory infection (Isla has been off school ill). Right thigh bearable, just but went slowly, worse going downhill.
First tentative run in a week, could feel thigh and calves on right purposefully slow as a consequence and focusing on form.

Went very carefully, particularly on downhills, due to dodgy right thigh, didn't feel great and whilst I focused on landing on balls of feet and engaging thigh my right calf and glute ended up aching a fair bit. GOing to have to be careful.
GPS tracking failed on phone so an estimate. Wary of running too far/hard as right thigh feels dodgy, took it relatively easy as a consequence.
Lazy start to the day, was going to further but couldn't be arsed. Legs a little achey, nothing specific though, didn't push myself.
Pleased with time, obviously faster on solid ground, slightly less hill but still had to go up Heeley Green, made up time going down to Sheffield College. Slight wheeze on chest.
Not too bad, felt I could push a bit and dull ache in right thigh not there, pleased with time, might try harder next time!
Felt tired (several late nights in a row drinking) right thigh had a mild ache throughout the run. Not trying hard hence slow time.
Not too bad, minor twinges but nothing serious, hills hard again!
Short and sweet, but not very fast!
Late start as didn't want to go out in the dark then dozed, probably did my good, decent pace in first 4km then hill, but felt ok. Didn't do wider loop in Graves though.
Did not want to get up and go running this morning but forced myself, not fast, had a stitch in right side for first few km. Poor nights sleep
First 5km were good, for some reason lagged on the sixth, but picked up a bit afterwards (probably as I knew I was going slow).
Felt good, no deep/heavy phlegm in the back of my throat, bit snotty but ran well, kept up pace, pause in Herdings Park for bodyweight machine exercise. Pleased with time.
Hills were hard work (they never get easier!), mild aches in knees, right inside hip/groin a little tender before starting.
Hilly! no major aches or pains, put effort in reflected in time.
Not too bad, no major aches or pains.
Not bad, minor twinges/aches in left knee and hip/groin. Bumped into Andes in Graves Park which was nice.
Short lunch time run, would have liked to have gone further but there.
Not bad, strange pain in back of right thigh near start but went away.
Not bad, a couple of stops to cough and clear lungs, right knee a little twinge near end but only towards end of downhill section.
Felt ok, no aches or pains in knees or hips.
Felt fairly good, less coughing for once! Outside right hip a little strange early on.
Not bad, didn't push hard after long run on Monday, knees and hips pretty good.

Hills were hard work, enjoyed Lord's Seat to Brown Knoll but right hip tendons (inner thigh) started hurting, pushed through and eased off, Kinder South was ok, realised I kept on slowing to walk unconsciously, so made effort not to. Both legs tendons on inner thigh at hip quite sore and pretty much walked from Hope Cross to Win Hill, made some effort to jog down to station but not at all fast. Back left around kidney area was tender/tight. Stretched on finishing will do more tonight.
Hard work as always on the hills, couple of pauses to clear throat but good pace overall.
Slightly different route, hills were hard, lungs still not working properly.
Not bad, still got horrible phlegm in the morning and had several pauses to cough/hack shit up but focused on form (getting good at that!) and half decent time in the end.
Cooler run, very misty, felt good once going (but typically didn't want to start!)
Much easier without hills, kept focus on form, lost it in places but got back on it. Couple of pauses for navigation.
Complete focus on form as lungs still not back to normal, quite a bit off normal pace but hey ho, at least I can run!
First run post COVID (first +ve test [2022-08-27 Sat]), hard work, chest noticeably tight on uphill sections and slow on first km which is mostly downhill, focused on form and got round.
Hard work, didn't want to go out but forced myself. Hot and humid, sweated buckets, not a fun run.
Left knee and inside right hip a little sore half way round, maintained focus on form.
Not a bad run, hard uphill to start but kept a decent pace.
Too late a start, very hot, sweating buckets, felt terrible. Left knee sore at start.
Left knee a little sore at start but abated quickly, right thigh/butt stiff later in the day (posture at desk?)
Not a great run, felt tired and lethargic, it was quite hot too. Lots of pauses.
Birthday run, nothing too hard, head-wind most of the way there and back strangely. Had a lie-down before turning round and coming back.
Not too bad, felt a bit sluggish, knackered after uphills.
Not bad, was very humid though and paused three times as a consequence (lazy really, just push on and take the hit on the time).
Felt tired and heavy, hard work and took a few breaks.
Not keen to go again but did it anyway, not too bad in the end.
Uphills felt hard but felt fairly good.
Not a bad run, head down and got on with it, focused on form when the going got tough.
Felt ok, light drizzle which was cooling and nice.

Started fast on first few km but then needed a shit after about 4km, very uncomfortable and slow as a consequence, had to keep stopping then head home early. Did another 3km afterwards. But damn hot throughout > 20C.
Hot and hard work, slow as a consequence, not much fun.
Middle of the day, damn hot, few slow passes when meeting others on the paths.
Legs tired from Snowdon Horseshoe at the weekend and hot even at 07:00 generally ok though.
Hot today, but kept a steady pace, required a bit more effort at the end but half decent pace overall for the steep route.
Good run, hot but kept it steady.
Another early run, kind of forced myself out to do it, but felt good, left hip no pain or discomfort at all, bit slower than normal but that's ok.
Not too bad, hard going up hill but kept going, paused twice for upper body workout (Herdings & Millhouses Parks), fairly good form throughout.
Again felt sluggish to start with. Pace picked up once going down hill but uphills felt hard.
Not so keen to head out again, but once started ok, knees and hips feel ok, felt slow uphill but most were sub-6min so not too bad.
Again didn't want to head out but was ok once going, fairly good pace, knees and hips ok.
Didn't want to run this morning but was ok after starting, bit slow but focusing on form and keeping going.
Felt good, went hard, several dog walkers, one caused pause. Knee and hip felt ok, was focusing on form.
Didn't want to head out but did, not too bad, felt heavy, strong headwinds for much of the run and lots of uphill (1241m apparently!).
Didn't feel like running today, bloated and lots of food still in stomach, pushed round and not too bad in the end. Left knee slightly better.
Did not want to go running this morning but forced myself, purposefully short and slow (hills helped there!). Left knee still a bit weird.
Felt good, slight twinge in right ankle around 9km as started down Derbyshire Lane, bumped into Jon Buck & Chester.
Good run, paused at Herdings to do some upper body weights on machine but kept going otherwise, left knee little weird on front outer left-hand side but not painful, hips and legs not sore either.
Felt good, kept going no pauses for stretching. Knees and hips ok.

Lot of uphill which was very steep, particularly Hen Cloud. Stopped to take lots of pictures too. Enjoyable run, even the last couple of km uphill back to the campsite. Shame about other aspects of the camping weekend.
Short, flatter run, pushed harder.
Felt good, focus on form paid off, knees and hips holding up well.
Lots of up and down, felt hard work, body is aching from previous days battle on Tower Chimney.
Annoyingly GPS dropped out again on fast downhill section, editing & importing didn't work. Felt good, neither knees nor hips sore, bit heavy towards end.
Felt good, couple of pauses on steep hills but no knee or hip pain and stayed focused on form 90% of the time.
GPS dropout again going into Cat Lane Woods, annoying. Extra loop on the circuit, felt slow/sluggish with heavy legs today, reflected in the time :-/
GPS dropped out after first km going up hill, estimated time. Legs felt a bit heavy/sluggish, could be the previous days cycle. Knees and hips generally ok though.
Ok, felt a bit slow up-hill, knees and hips generally good, focused on form. Being early evening I could feel lunch (two fried egg sandwiches & beer).
Early run but felt good, kept an eye on form and no knee or hip pains, even on downhill, have to not over do it though.
Pauses at tops of hills, twinges in left knee on downhills, have to stay focused on form.
Very steep hill which was mostly walked, quite a few stops and some back-tracking for navigation.
Early run, didn't really want to go out but forced myself. Felt good after a few kms though, no pauses today.
New trainers! Tried a bit harder on hills, felt sick near top so pause to stretch, good time overall. Very hot at end when stretching.
Set of intending to do 10-12km but left knee was twinging so went shorter. Ok pace, still have lingering phlegm on chest, annoying.
Felt good again, pushed through without any pauses.
Felt good, didn't pause for any stretches, legs going well at end. Enjoyed being up and out early.
Felt good, legs strong throughout, one pause at top of hill.
Hard work! More hills than going up Leighton Road, was mindful of knees and focused on form, harder on the downhills though.
Felt better than recently, had some energy in my legs throughout most of the run but focused on good form.
Missed tracking a section so doubled back and ran it twice noting times. Legs and knees not too bad.
Felt ok, legs a little sluggish in first few km, going slow on purpose and focusing on form.
Legs felt tired, but was concentrating on form and landing on ball of foot (calves still tight), left knee started to twinge around 8km.
Purposefully took it easy, smaller strides, landing on balls of feet as much as possible (required regular focus).
Few pauses to decide which way to go, not too bad, knee held up and didn't ache lots afterwards.
Purposefully slow and focusing on form as first run in 10 days after left knee hurting. Really need a better office chair. GPS missed two sections through woods at start, mildly-annoying.
Tired after big cycle on Wednesday but pushed through focusing on form. Felt knees a bit, will see how they are later/tomorrow.
Felt sluggish, left knee hurting again.
Cold, wet and windy, slippery underfoot to start too. Fast on downhill (4.02m/km would have been sub-four if there hadn't been a fallen tree).
Felt good, was going to go further but thought better of it, best to keep most runs short.
Felt ok, knee not hurting as much, focused on form, bit slower than usual uphills.
Cold and icey, wary of knee so went slow purposefully went slow.
Conscious of knee being sore and slightly swollen therefore purposefully went slow focusing on form which I've let slip a bit of late.
Didn't push too hard as left knee has been sore of late, nice to do a longer run, 2 pauses, one for navigation one for photo.
Hard work on the hills!
Again headed out intending to do slightly longer run, focusing on form. Good pace half-way round so switched to shorter run.
Started slow on purpose, picked up time on downhill at the end, felt good.
Paused to stretch, need to do a lap pushing through at same pace.
Was going to go for longer run and focused on form, this set good pace to kept focus and switched to usual 6.5km circuit, good time :-)
Windy and damp, paused a few times to stretch but pushed on through other points where I felt like stopping. Leg and hips ok, must stretch more through the day though.
Really wasn't in the mood but glad I went out anyway, focused on form which is working well for me.
Really focused on form, landing on ball of foot, pushing off for slightly longer strides, worked well.
Purposefully didn't push myself today, felt ok-ish, bit of effort required up the long hill though.
Felt ok, bit tired, hips and legs ok, more effort stretching on rest days is required.
Harder going, but then more up-hill and did run yesterday, plus slippery underfoot in the woods. Felt ok though, even if not as fast, have to be careful and remember to stretch tonight and tomorrow.
Felt good, focused on form, went fast :-)
Unusual pains in stomach, probably the crisps I ate an hour before hand, lesson learned!
Felt really good, not thinking about pace, focusing on form, yet went fast.
Good run, didn't push too hard, focused on form, still got decent time, think I need to watch/be mindful of hips (right one this time).
Cold, wet and slushy! Did ok considering conditions. No stopping at all.
GPS playing up, only logged as 6.08km but I know from last few weeks its longer than that so have adjusted. Felt ok, not too out of breath.
